# Git Sync With Main

Before **starting a new phase/ticket** or **pushing a feature branch**, sync with `main`:

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b cursor/phase-N-<summary>   # new work only
# OR for an existing branch:
git checkout cursor/phase-N-<summary>
git merge origin/main                      # or: git rebase origin/main
```

## When to sync

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Start implementing a new phase/ticket | Pull latest `main`, branch from it |
| Before `git push` on a feature branch | Merge or rebase `origin/main` into the branch, resolve conflicts, re-run tests |
| After a PR is merged while you have open work | Sync `main`, then merge into your feature branch |

## Push checklist

1. `git fetch origin && git merge origin/main` (on feature branch)
2. `./scripts/lint.sh`
3. Run backend + frontend tests
4. `git push` only if all checks pass

Never push a feature branch that is behind `main` without syncing first.
